{
  "red_failure_evidence": "BEFORE THIS CELL: parse_response (src/herdr/socket.rs) read only error.message from a refusal envelope and returned HerdrError::Request(message). error.code was never read by any line of the codebase -- git show HEAD:src/herdr/socket.rs shows the error branch with no reference to the code field at all. Consequence: agent_name_taken, workspace_not_found, tab_create_failed and every other upstream code were indistinguishable from each other and from a local transport failure, so no caller could branch on any of them. PRE-CHANGE CHECK THAT FAILED: cargo test --quiet --lib -- errcode_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([5-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed' on the untouched tree printed \"running 0 tests / test result: ok. 0 passed; 173 filtered out\" and the guard grep exited 1 -- no test carrying the errcode_ prefix existed, so the verify could not pass by accident on an already-green suite. A SECOND, UNPLANNED RED was recorded mid-cell: the worker first shipped a socket test that awaited accept() before issuing the client call, with no read timeout in call() to break the wait; the orchestrator killed the suite after 10 minutes and returned the cell.",
  "green_evidence": {
    "command": "cargo test --quiet && cargo fmt --all --check && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test --lib -- errcode_ | grep -qE 'test result: ok. ([5-9]|[1-9][0-9]+) passed'",
    "run_by": "orchestrator, independently, after the worker reported",
    "output": "cargo test --quiet: 180 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored (173 before this cell). cargo fmt --all --check: silent. cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings: silent. errcode_-only: test result: ok. 7 passed; 0 failed; 173 filtered out. Guard grep exit code: 0."
  },
  "behavior_change_description": "Before: every refusal herdr sent back -- whatever its code -- collapsed into HerdrError::Request carrying only the message; error.code was read by nothing and discarded. After: parse_response reads error.code and maps agent_name_taken, workspace_not_found and invalid_agent_argv to their own variants, and every other code to Remote{code,message} with the code string intact. HerdrError::Request is unchanged and still means 'we failed to make the request' (serialize, connect, write, read).",
  "observable_difference": "A caller can now recognise an agent-name collision and retry with a new name instead of seeing an opaque request failure -- which is what makes the create verbs in the following cells possible at all. Operators also see the code herdr actually sent rather than only its prose.",
  "regression_guard": "parse_response_maps_error, the one pre-existing test asserting the old message-only collapse, was deliberately updated rather than deleted; it now asserts the Remote mapping for an unknown code. errcode_missing_code_is_remote_not_malformed guards the rule that a refusal without a code never becomes Malformed, and errcode_local_io_failure_still_maps_to_request guards that local transport failures still map to Request. The two typed-variant tests assert the server's own message survives into the variant, not just the code.",
  "reviewer_note": "Caught during orchestrator review and fixed before capping: the first implementation preserved error.code but dropped error.message for agent_name_taken and workspace_not_found, producing operator-facing strings like 'agent name already in use: ' with nothing after the colon. For agent_name_taken herdr's message enumerates the conflicting terminals, which is the most useful thing a human could be told; discarding it repeated the same class of loss this cell exists to repair. Both variants now carry the message."
